## Coding Guidelines (Soft Preferences)

### React / Dashboard
- Prefer functional components with hooks
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes over custom CSS
- PascalCase for component files (`LoginForm.tsx`)
- Keep components small and focused

### FastAPI / Backend
- Prefer async functions for endpoints
- Use Pydantic models for request/response validation
- Consistent error responses: `{"success": bool, "data": ..., "error": ...}`

### Extension (Plasmo)
- Follow Plasmo conventions for popup/contents/background
- Use Chrome Storage API for local persistence
- Sync preferences with dashboard via API

### Accessibility (We're Building an A11y Tool!)
- Use semantic HTML (`button`, `nav`, `main`) not div soup
- Ensure keyboard navigation for interactive elements
- Add ARIA labels for non-obvious UI elements

## Git Workflow

### Branch Strategy (CRITICAL)
- **NEVER work on main** — Always create/use a feature branch first
- One branch per feature, continue working in existing branch until merged
- Available branches: `feat/auth`, `feat/tracking`, `feat/agents`

### Branch Naming
- Features: `feat/short-description`
- Fixes: `fix/what-broke`
- Experiments: `exp/idea-name`

### Commit Messages
- Present tense, descriptive: "Add login form", "Fix button crash"
- Avoid vague messages: "fix stuff", "updates"

### AI/Cursor Workflow
- AI commits locally only — NEVER pushes automatically
- Developer reviews commits and pushes manually
- Always verify branch before making changes: `git branch`

### Daily Habits
- Pull `main` at start of day
- **ALWAYS create a feature branch before coding** — never commit to main directly
- Work on your own feature branch
- Commit every 30-60 minutes
- Push manually when ready

### Before Merging
- Pull latest `main` into your branch
- Test that everything works
- Merge to main and push (manually)

## API Endpoints (Reference)

```
POST /api/auth/login, /signup, /logout
GET  /api/auth/me

GET/POST /api/user/preferences

POST /api/compliance/scan
GET  /api/compliance/scan/{id}
GET  /api/compliance/scan/{id}/issues
POST /api/compliance/fix

POST /api/tracking/event
GET  /api/tracking/analytics
```

## Quick Reference

**⚠️ First step for ANY task: `git checkout -b feat/your-feature`**

| Action | Command |
|--------|---------|
| **Start feature (ALWAYS FIRST!)** | `git checkout -b feat/name` |
| Save work | `git add . && git commit -m "message"` |
| Push branch | `git push origin feat/name` |
| Sync with main | `git pull origin main` |
| Merge to main | `git checkout main && git merge feat/name` |

## Remember
- Speed matters, but so does a working demo
- When in doubt, communicate with the team
- See `docs/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` for full details
